A subsequence means you can delete some (or no) characters from t without changing the order of the remaining characters to get s. 
Use two pointers: i → for string s. j → for string t. Traverse t:
If characters match → move both pointers. Otherwise → move only j If i reaches end of s, return true

class Solution {
    public boolean isSubsequence(String s, String t) {
        int i = 0;
        int j = 0; 
        while (i < s.length() && j < t.length()) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j)) {
                i++;
            }
            j++;
        }
        return i == s.length();
    }
}
